  "description": "<i>Spaced Weller</i> is a puzzle game where the player must create coloured lines on a magical grid. The grid consists of 7x6 spheres and the players gets points for each row that consists of at least three spheres. Row can be formed either horizontally, vertically or diagonally. When no more lines can be formed it is the next players turn. The round is complete when the time runs out.<br><br>There are three special spheres:<ul><li><b>Purple spheres</b> that acts as obstacles</li>\n<li><b>Blitter spheres</b> that can be used to destroy opponents spheres and purple spheres</li>\n<li><b>Bonus spheres</b> that gives extra points once they are included in a line</li></ul>\nThe game was written in STOS.",
